The paper focuses on developing a deep learning model for emotion recognition in humanoid robots for human-robot interaction. This involves computer vision (CV) for recognizing facial expressions and body language, robotics (RO) for implementing the model in a humanoid robot, human-computer interaction (HC) for designing the system to interact with humans, machine learning (LG) for optimizing the hyperparameters of the model, and artificial intelligence (AI) for developing the overall intelligent system. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV and cs.RO, followed by cs.HC, cs.LG, and cs.AI.
